        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Per the Highway Traffic Act of Ontario, ‚Äústunt driving‚Äù can include actually performing a stunt behind the wheel of a car, or betting on race/contest on a roadway. So, they call street racing ‚Äústunt driving‚Äù because Canada.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2021/11/Ontario-Police-Bust-Stunt-Drivers-3.jpg",
        "width": 1920,
        "height": 1080
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "In one incident, York Regional Police posted to its official, verified Twitter account that a red Corvette was clocked going 128 km/h, which is about 79 mph. We don‚Äôt know what the posted limited was, but we‚Äôll assume it was well under that speed.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2021/11/Ontario-Police-Bust-Stunt-Drivers-2.jpg",
        "width": 1920,
        "height": 1080
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "A release from the department says 25 drivers were charged with stunt driving over the weekend of November 5-7. The vehicles were impounded for 14 days and the drivers were arrested. Other charges were added in there, including dangerous driving and speeding.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "And here we thought Canadians were extra nice and courteous.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2021/11/Ontario-Police-Bust-Stunt-Drivers-4.jpg",
        "width": 1920,
        "height": 1080
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "OPP Highway Safety Division also took to Twitter with its official, verified account to show how a 22-year-old driver in a Mazda was clocked going 174 km/h on Highway 8. We don‚Äôt know what the speed limit is there, but that‚Äôs about 108 mph, which we think is probably a fair bit above what they‚Äôre supposed to be going. That person picked up a stunt driving charge along with speeding and novice driver BAC above zero or in other words a blood alcohol level that wasn‚Äôt zero. Not good. That last charge comes with a 24-hour suspension of the driver‚Äôs license.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The lesson here is that even in Canada they have problems with stunting or street racing. Also, they have funny names for things.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
